{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:49:42.598Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"869b2lqy","input":{"summary":"I have completed a comprehensive review and validation of the Billing and Invoice Metadata CRUD APIs task (Task ID: 138-phase5-api-billing-invoices-crud). \n\n### Implementation & Verification Details:\n1. **API Endpoints Built & Verified**:\n   - `GET /api/v1/invoices`: Returns list of invoices with pagination/filtering. Accessible by authenticated users with role-based checks. \n   - `POST /api/v1/invoices`: Permits billing or finance managers to issue invoices. Restricts write access for standard client roles. Includes automatic parameter generation, validation checks on `client_id`, `amount`, and unique `invoice_number` check.\n   - `GET /api/v1/invoices/[id]`: Retrieve single invoice with deep tenant-isolation checks (clients can only read their associated client invoices).\n   - `PATCH /api/v1/invoices/[id]`: Permit update of specific fields with schema validation.\n   - `DELETE /api/v1/invoices/[id]`: Permit deletion of invoice entries for admin/finance roles.\n2. **Access Control & Tenant Isolation**: Built robust tenant checks with JWT parsing logic, verifying client token association against the simulated resource-owner ID, and enforcing strict 403 Forbidden status on unauthorized cross-tenant operations.\n3. **Query Filters Supported**: Successfully filtered on `client_id`, `project_id`, `status`, `month`, `start_date`, `end_date`, and generic text `search`.\n4. **Integration Testing**: Designed and executed an integration test suite `scripts/test-invoice-apis.js` executing real GET, POST, PATCH, and DELETE requests, asserting tenant-isolation, filter validations, and status-level constraints.\n5. **No regressions**: Confirmed the entire Next.js codebase compiles, lints successfully (`npm run lint` passed), and maintains maximum design compliance with the GFF AI Premium Enterprise aesthetic. No modifications were made to the approved landing page or slug routing.","verified":true}}}
